&gt; I found the book.
&gt; 
&gt; It is called &quot;The Diary and Sundry Observations of Thomas Alva
Edison&quot; the copyright for the edition I have is 1948. Since only a
limited number of 1st printings have Chapter 8, &quot;The Realms Beyond&quot;,
then I suspect 1948 would be the date of the first printing.
&gt; 
&gt; Each chapter ends with the year Mr. Edison wrote it (it is primarily
his diary). The part about spirit communication is dated 1922.
&gt; 
&gt; Obviously a 61 year old book is a bit fragile so I&#39;ll start trying
to scan those pages but I&#39;m not going to hurt the book for it.
